22 SUMMARY
2233 This bill requires emergency medical services educators and emergency medical
2244 services training centers to be licensed by the Emergency Medical Services' Board. Current
2255 law provides that a person who operates or practices without a license commits a Class E
2266 crime. The bill specifies that a person must intentionally, knowingly or recklessly operate
2277 or practice without a license to commit a Class E crime. The bill also provides for a civil
2288 violation for operating or practicing without a license. It requires rather than allows
2299 physicians and hospitals to report trauma information to the board and amends the
3300 definition of "regional council" to specify that a council is an entity rather than a business
3311 entity.
